- Variability -
Customer Transactions: The number and types of transactions change during the day, week, or month.
Financial Markets: The values of stocks and other investments go up and down.
Economic Conditions: Economic changes affect interest rates and the bank's overall stability.

- Complexity -
Products and Services: Banks offer different types of accounts and services, each with its own rules.
Regulatory Compliance: Banks have to follow many financial rules.
Risk Management: Banks use strategies to deal with different types of risks.

- Interconnectedness -
Customers and Accounts: Customer accounts are connected to various services.
Interbank Relationships: Banks have connections with other financial institutions.
Technology: Information systems link different bank branches and services.